        output='Based on the provided text, here is the retrieved "Description of Capital Stock" section, outlining the company\'s (Space Exploration Technologies Corp.) capital structure post-IPO.\n\n### **Authorized Capital Stock**\nUpon completion of the offering, the authorized capital stock consists of:\n*   **Class A Common Stock:** 36,132,150,000 shares authorized, par value $0.001 per share.\n*   **Class B Common Stock:** 6,125,000,000 shares authorized, par value $0.001 per share.\n*   **Class C Common Stock:** 10,000,000,000 shares authorized, par value $0.001 per share.\n*   **Preferred Stock:** 2,400,000,000 shares authorized, par value $0.001 per share. No shares will be issued and outstanding upon completion of the offering.\n\n### **Voting Rights & Dual-Class Structure**\nThe company has a dual-class common stock structure:\n*   **Class A Common Stock:** One vote per share.\n*   **Class B Common Stock:** Ten votes per share.\n*   **Class C Common Stock:** No voting rights (except as required by law).\n*   **Class D Common Stock:** Voting rights will be established if and when issued by the Board.\n\n**Class B Special Voting Rights:** Holders of Class B common stock, voting as a separate class, are entitled to elect 51% of the authorized directors (rounded up).\n\n### **Key Terms for Common Stock**\n*   **Dividends:** Paid pro rata, on an equal priority, *pari passu* basis to Class A, B, and C holders, subject to rights of any senior securities.\n*   **Liquidation:** Holders of Class A, B, and C share ratably in assets after payment of liabilities and senior securities\' liquidation preferences.\n*   **Conversion:** Each share of Class B is convertible at the holder\'s option into one share of Class A. Class B shares also automatically convert to Class A upon any transfer (other than certain permitted transfers). Class A and Class C shares are not convertible.\n*   **Preemptive Rights:** None for Class A, B, or C holders.\n\n### **Preferred Stock**\nThe board is authorized to issue preferred stock in one or more series with rights, preferences, and limitations determined at the time of issuance, without further shareholder approval.\n\n### **Special Provisions & Anti-Takeover Effects**\n*   **Additional Class B Shares:** Future issuance of Class B common stock is restricted to Mr. Musk, his family members, and certain permitted entities.\n*   **Charter Protections:** Removal of Mr. Musk from his board/leadership roles (CEO and Chairman) requires approval from a majority of the Class B voting power, voting as a class.\n*   **Charter Amendments:** Amendments affecting the rights of Class B common stock (including rights of Class B Directors) require approval from Class B stockholders voting as a class.\n\n---\n**Note:** This retrieval synthesizes information from the provided text fragments. The "issued and outstanding" share counts were typically left blank (`         shares`) in the prospectus sections, as they are determined post-offering. The capitalization table and notes reference specific numbers at various dates (e.g., March 31, 2026, December 31, 2025) which reflect the company\'s authorized shares following historical stock splits and the merger with xAI.',
